post_text:
We want to thank our community for the overwhelming support in our bond issue. As advertised we will be making some great improvements with the funds generated from this bond.
1) Upgrades to our agriculture building, and bathrooms/ concession areas at the livestock show barn.
2) New HVAC units in elementary and flooring in elem gymnasium.
3)Press boxes for Softball and Baseball fields - and much needed drainage work will be completed.
4)Van for transportation of smaller groups of students
5)New pick-up for FFA program.
5)Upgrade phone system district wide.

All of these items will give our students a better experience and education. None of it would be possible without the great support of our parents and community. Thank you very much.

post_text: Elementary Parents: Thank you SO much for your patience with all of the changes today! We realize that car line was CRAZY, so we are going back to one exit point for all students at the usual spot at the south end of the building. Older students will be called by radio ahead of time to come to the south end of the building, which eliminates the need for two pick-up points. We hope this will help in the speed in which students are picked up and decreases the amount of time you will have to wait in the line. The route will be posted on the Town of Stratford and Stratford Police Department FaceBook pages. Again, we thank you for your patience as we work through these things and work to provide a safe and healthy space for your children!

post_text:
MIDDLE SCHOOL AND HIGH SCHOOL ONLINE ENROLLMENT OPENS TOMORROW

*If you already have an account from enrolling an elementary school student, you can access your MS and HS students to enroll them here as well.

*If you already have a Wen-Gage parent account for checking grades from last year, this should be the same account you use to enroll. (Access the Student Records Portal)

*If you need an account setup or your login from last year isn't working, please email enrollment@stratford.k12.ok.us if you haven't already done so and list your name and student name(s) and grade(s). We are returning emails as they are received.

*Follow the instructions as listed

* MS and HS enrollment links will be visible tomorrow

* No paper copies available this year. If you need assistance with online enrollment or don't have a device or internet, then you can visit the school office between the hours of 10-2.

*Reply back to enrollment@stratford.k12.ok.us if you encounter problems or you can send a message through the Remind App or FB Messenger.

post_text:
STRATFORD MIDDLE SCHOOL... looking ahead

Tomorrow morning we will be posting a brief video of Mrs. McClaflin addressing the Distance Learning program that will start Monday, April 6th.

A Parent/Student Guide will also be posted to help get students and parents started with the program.

In the meantime, teachers are contacting parents and students to touch base with them about what is to come.

There are a few REMIND changes so make sure you have those classes up to date so teachers can communicate with you and student. (The updated list will be posted tomorrow as well.)

Thank you for being patient with us! We want the best for our students and have put a lot of thought into developing a plan to move forward.

PK - April 2 from 10:00-12:00 @ car line door
KG - April 6 from 10:00-12:00 @ car line door
1st - April 7 from 10:00-12:00 @ car line door
2nd - April 8 from 10:00-12:00 @ car line door

Attention Stratford JOM Students and Parents:
Marksmanship Clinic
The Chickasaw Nation will host a Marksmanship Clinic 9 a.m.-2 p.m., Sep. 15 at the Davis Shooting Sports Club in Davis.
Chickasaw youth ages 12-18 are eligible to apply.
The marksmanship clinic offers a broad range of skill development for beginners as well as experienced youth interested in firearm sports. This clinic with emphasize on teaching basic shooting techniques and fundamentals.
During the clinic, students will put their aim and technique to the test while enjoying the Olympic sport of skeet shooting. Students will practice marksmanship by firing at sporting clays under strict supervision.
For more information, or to apply, contact youth services at (580) 310-6620.

post_text:
Attention 7th-12th Grade Students:
The Chickasaw Nation Science, Technology, Engineering and Math (STEM) Academy will host a biology and genetics workshop for students (all students - not tribal exclusive) in grades seven through 12, Friday, June 29, 6-10 p.m. and Saturday, June 30, 8-11 a.m.
This workshop is for students who have an interest in science. Chickasaw citizen and evolutionary biologist, Dr. Chris Hamilton, will share a presentation about bats and hawk moths, how they have evolved for survival and how their evolution is related to the future of biology and medicine.
The presentations will take place at the Chickasaw Nation STEM Academy, 301 Seabrook Road, Ada, Oklahoma.
Breakfast and dinner will be provided. The workshops are offered to students at no cost.
RSVP is recommended.
For more information, call (580) 272-5579. Email STEM@chicksasaw.net to RSVP.
To learn more about Dr. Hamiltonâ€™s work, visit 8legs2fangs.com.

post_text: We are starting to see some cases of flu in Stratford Schools. To help, talk to your child about washing their hands frequently and not drinking or eating after others. Also, make sure you and your children are vaccinated against the flu. Finally, if your child has the #Flu, please keep them home to prevent the spread to others. School board policy requires students to stay home for 24 hours after last fever (without the help of Tylenol or Motrin).
